rename.to: Build wheel  with OpenVINO  ERROR: testRegisterCustomOpsLibrary (__main__.TestInferenceSession)

body: @jywu-msft @MaajidKhan can one of you take a look?

After   update install  OpenVINO 2021.02   the error message become :   

generate_onnx: ./dev_paul/user_config\A\model-02011408-epoch47-7.5464.onnx
2021-03-30 16:13:23.0999880 [E:onnxruntime:Default, provider_bridge_ort.cc:608 onnxruntime::ProviderLibrary::Get] Failed to load library, error code: 126

Hello @hcgprague. I tried reproducing the same environment on windows from my side (onnxruntime with OpenVINO 2020.4 version) and it worked fine for me. I was able to infer a python sample as well. I believe your installation process was wrong, please follow the steps from this page: https://www.onnxruntime.ai/docs/how-to/build.html#openvino I will try to quickly add the steps I followed to make things more clear. **1. Initialize the OpenVINO on windows (Any OpenVINO version)** C:\ \bin\setupvars.bat **Note:** It's advisable to use Developer command prompt for VS 2019 2. > **git clone https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime.git** > **cd onnxruntime** > **build.bat --config Release --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019" --use_openvino CPU_FP32 --build_shared_lib build_wheel --parallel --skip_tests** > **cd build\Windows\Release\Release** > Run your python/cpp applications from here **Note:** OpenVINO-EP is still not supported with pip installation. please try out the above steps and it would work fine even with the latest OpenVINO Binary version you were trying with. Attaching sample screenshots of my build and my inferencing output with python sample for reference.

1.Yes, I could run  webapi.py  with openvino .   
2.But after using pyinstaller==4.0 to make webapi.exe   ,  when it(.exe)  run would appear  load lib error as :
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19700407/114137357-a5959d80-993e-11eb-87f8-0513e841cad2.png)
Hi @hcgprague . can you use the latest **OpenVINO 2021.3 installation package** for windows and re-build onnxruntime-openvino execution provider on windows.

After I reinstall   OpenVINO 2021.3  , and     before execute onnxruntime_shared_lib_test.exe    ,  I have to    run  setupvars.bat   in C:\Program Files (x86)\Intel\openvino_2021.3.394\bin.

Test would be pass.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19700407/114673940-503ffe80-9d39-11eb-95f7-178e624851fb.png)

And  I could run onnxruntime_openvino prediction  successfully in my project  of VSCODE   by  pip install   onnxruntime_openvino-1.7.0-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl     from C:\onnxruntime\build\Windows\Release\Release\dist .



![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19700407/114674886-44a10780-9d3a-11eb-80e8-f618127762b4.png)
But After pyinstaller to package to   webapi.exe  ,  it run start with error as      2021-04-14 16:00:19.1906275 [E:onnxruntime:Default, provider_bridge_ort.cc:564 onnxruntime::ProviderSharedLibrary::Ensure] Failed to load library, error code: 126


![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19700407/114675382-bbd69b80-9d3a-11eb-99aa-c2d90a3627a6.png)

Hi @hcgprague .
Glad that you were able to run the tests and infer your python sample.

coming to the last issue, where you trying to convert a .py file to .exe using pyinstaller python library on windows.
I think this issue is different and specific to windows and has to do with use of external python library. can you create a separate ticket for this issue.

And you can close this, if you don't have any other issue using onnxruntime with openvino on windows.
